Contributor: mcliquid Discussion Comment No.: 1 Comment: Hi, please note: changesets should be local. To avoid conflicts and as a courtesy to reviewers, it is recommended to: • combine changes in a small geographical area (within a city, district or province) • keep changes within the same country • upload/save changes before moving on to map in a different area Why? Have a look at the section "Geographical size of changesets" on this wiki page: https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Changeset Thanks for considering, have a nice day and happy mapping! Date: 2024-02-04T10:16:38+01:00
